by gas accretion (i.e., an active galactic nucleus\n[AGN]), Sw J2058+05 would seem to represent a new mode of variability in these\nsources, as the observed properties appear largely inconsistent with known\nclasses of AGNs capable of generating relativistic jets (blazars, narrow-line\nSeyfert 1 galaxies).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2011 20:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Apr 2012 03:27:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 4 May 2012 04:20:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
